Hello

Unfortunately, my two previous requests didn't fix the issue - but to be
honest, they were just guesses from my side what might solve the problem.

But now I did some deep research with the tool hda-analyser, and found out
that changing node 0x17 from the default of 0x06 to 0x02 does indeed fix
the problem, and the volume control now correctly changes the volume of
upper and lower speakers, not just the lower ones.

Node 0x17 seems to be the balance between the upper and lower speakers,
where the other settings (0x03 and 0x08) result in way to little volume in
the lower speakers, resulting in a thin, low-end-lacking sound output.
Changing from the default 0x06 to 0x02 does indeed change the sound
slightly - just enough that I can hear a difference, but I'm not entirely
sure what it changes. I think 0x02 has the upper loudspeakers ever so
slightly louder than 0x06. It's not ideal that 0x02 changes the sound
slightly, but it's easily worth the functioning volume control.

I did verify that this change does not affect the sound of connected
headphones.

[image: image.png]

Best regards,
--Sandro

